message: "If you use this repository, please cite the software artifact below."
title: "Moral Attention Reallocation in Language Models"
type: software
version: "v0.1-confirmation"
date-released: 2026-04-12
license: Apache-2.0
authors:
  - family-names: Zhu
    given-names: Hanzhen
    email: hanzhen@umich.edu
repository-code: "https://github.com/hanzhenzhujene/moral-attention-reallocation"
url: "https://github.com/hanzhenzhujene/moral-attention-reallocation"
abstract: >-
  A pre-freeze research artifact for studying whether framing conditions
  reallocate moral attention in language models toward inward motive and
  disposition rather than outward behavioral surface. The current public
  confirmation slice uses a Christian heart-focused condition as the main
  probe.
keywords:
  - llm evaluation
  - moral reasoning
  - moral psychology
  - benchmark design
  - framing effects
